# Privacy Policy — PagePocket

**Last updated: April 2026**

## Overview

PagePocket is a Chrome extension that captures web pages and saves them as PDF, PNG, or JPEG files. This policy explains how the extension handles your data.

## Data Collected

PagePocket does not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.

The extension captures the visible content of the current tab and saves it directly to your downloads folder. No page content, screenshots, or files are stored by the extension or sent anywhere.

## Data Storage

PagePocket does not use any browser storage APIs. No data persists between sessions.

## Data Sharing

No data is collected, transmitted, or shared with any external server, service, or third party.

All processing happens locally in your browser using bundled open-source libraries (html2canvas and jsPDF).

## Permissions

- **activeTab** - grants temporary access to the current tab when you click the capture button
- **scripting** - used to inject the html2canvas library into the page to render its content
- **downloads** - used to save the output file to your downloads folder
- **tabs** - used to read tab information and take screenshots during scroll & stitch capture
- **host_permissions (`<all_urls>`)** - required to inject scripts and capture pages on any site

## Changes to This Policy

This policy may be updated occasionally. The latest version will always be available at this URL.

